<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14119">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Kayaking.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8978">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8978 mb-requirement-id-8979">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the hazards you are most likely to
        encounter while participating in kayaking activities, including weather
        and water-related hazards, and what you should do to anticipate, help
        prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xUUX1VI7i1I" target="_blank"
          >Kayaking Tips—Cold Water and Winter Paddling (Wear, Gear, and Risks)
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/WMU4jNmlCQA" target="_blank"
          >Top 5 Kayak Safety Rules for Beginners (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8978 mb-requirement-id-8980">
        (b) Review prevention, symptoms, and first-aid treatment for the
        following injuries or illnesses that can occur while kayaking: blisters,
        cold-water shock and hypothermia, heat-related illnesses, dehydration,
        sunburn, sprains, and strains. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Kr2ouLj1oW0" target="_blank"
          >OSHA Heat Illness Prevention Campaign (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/u0sLzfq_w9s" target="_blank"
          >How To Treat a Sunburn (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/iLbL7fffGAk" target="_blank"
          >First Aid Kit for Kayaking—What's in It? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rH3gZuSr6Y8" target="_blank"
          >Cold Water Shock—How To Deal With Cold Water Shock (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8978 mb-requirement-id-8981">
        (c) Review the Scouting America Safety Afloat policy. Explain to your
        counselor how this applies to kayaking. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/safety-afloat/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Afloat (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8982">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Before doing requirements 3 through 8, successfully complete the Scouting
      America swimmer test. <br /><b>Note:</b> See the <i>Swimming</i> merit
      badge pamphlet for details about the Scouting America swimmer test.
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Swimming.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        ><i>Swimming</i> Merit Badge Pamphlet (PDF)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8948">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8948 mb-requirement-id-8949">
        (a) Review the characteristics of life jackets most appropriate for
        kayaking and understand why one must always be worn while paddling. Then
        demonstrate how to select and fit a life jacket for kayaking. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4y9XPNy1L1U" target="_blank"
          >How To Choose the Right Life Jacket (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8948 mb-requirement-id-8950">
        (b) Review the importance of safety equipment such as a signal device,
        extra paddle, sponge, bilge pump, flotation bags, and throw bag.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/L7DkmwqfcLI" target="_blank"
          >Essential Gear That All Paddlers Need To Carry On the Water
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-z_h6ShvsHU" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Safety: How To Use a Kayak Bilge Pump (How To Get Water out of
          Your Kayak) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xcl4I8V2Pfg" target="_blank"
          >Must Have Paddling Safety Gear | How To Kayak or Canoe (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8951">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8951 mb-requirement-id-8952">
        (a) Name and point out the major parts of a kayak. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JJGYUG8Bfxc" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Overview (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8951 mb-requirement-id-8953">
        (b) Review the differences in the design between recreational,
        whitewater, and sea or touring kayaks. Include how length, width,
        stability, and rocker are involved in the design of each type. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2xlCx8ckfR8" target="_blank"
          >How To Choose the Right Kayak for All Types of Flatwater Paddlers
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8951 mb-requirement-id-8954">
        (c) Explain the care, maintenance, and storage of a kayak. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DThGAXJ8hM8" target="_blank"
          >How To Clean and Maintain Your Kayak (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8956">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Discuss the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8956 mb-requirement-id-8957">
        (a) Correct methods for the use of a kayak paddle <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/RZLtB7BmNAc" target="_blank"
          >How To Hold a Kayak Paddle (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/v0-efrwppWQ" target="_blank"
          >Proper Technique for Paddling a Kayak (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8956 mb-requirement-id-8983">
        (b) Parts of a paddle <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.boat-ed.com/paddlesports/paddlesports/studyGuide/Kayak-Paddles/11109901_52043/"
          target="_blank"
          >Kayak Paddles (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8956 mb-requirement-id-8958">
        (c) The care and maintenance of a paddle <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://floridasplendors.com/kayak-paddle-maintenance-essential-tips/"
          target="_blank"
          >Kayak Paddle Maintenance (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8959">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Using a properly equipped kayak with an open cockpit, a sit-on-top, or an
      inflatable kayak, do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8959 mb-requirement-id-8960">
        (a) Safely capsize and perform a wet exit. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/blJFzirv3-E" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Wet Exit—How To Get Out of Your Kayak (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8959 mb-requirement-id-8961">
        (b) Reenter the kayak with assistance from a buddy boat. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/O_-a5ngnRew" target="_blank"
          >How To Re-Enter a Sit Inside Kayak for Beginners (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YSRCAdCSj8Q" target="_blank"
          >Sea Kayak T-Rescue: Deep Water Rescue / How To Get Back in Your Kayak
          With Help (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wE5y_DW2h04" target="_blank"
          >Master the Sea Kayak Scoop Rescue for Injured Paddlers (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/j-zpJQeiaNc" target="_blank"
          >Heel Hook—Kayak Rescue (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8959 mb-requirement-id-8962">
        (c) Demonstrate a kayak-over-kayak rescue. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YSRCAdCSj8Q" target="_blank"
          >Sea Kayak T-Rescue: Deep Water Rescue / How To Get Back in Your Kayak
          With Help (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8959 mb-requirement-id-8963">
        (d) Demonstrate the HELP position. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Z5X1K1I8xEc" target="_blank"
          >Help/Huddle Position (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8959 mb-requirement-id-8964">
        (e) Capsize the kayak, swim it and the paddle to shore, and empty water
        from the kayak with assistance if needed. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ykvS7iHeC_g" target="_blank"
          >White Water Kayak—Swim to Shore (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8965">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      As a solo paddler, use a properly equipped kayak to demonstrate the
      following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8965 mb-requirement-id-8966">
        (a) Forward stroke <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yz00070X04o" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Forward Stroke (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8965 mb-requirement-id-8967">
        (b) Backstroke <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/O-feCLPf-qw" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Reverse Stroke (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8965 mb-requirement-id-8968">
        (c) Forward sweep <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GWpaWh8AcZw" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Sweep Strokes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8965 mb-requirement-id-8969">
        (d) Reverse sweep <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/O-feCLPf-qw" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Reverse Stroke (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8965 mb-requirement-id-8970">
        (e) Draw stroke <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/H3G8Viju93I" target="_blank"
          >Kayak Draw Stroke—In Water Recovery (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8965 mb-requirement-id-8971">
        (f) Stern draw <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0bWe37-jaD8" target="_blank"
          >Stern Draw (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8972">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      As a solo paddler, use a properly equipped kayak to demonstrate the
      following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8972 mb-requirement-id-8973">
        (a) Paddle a straight line for 15 to 20 boat lengths using appropriate
        strokes while maintaining trim and balance of the kayak. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7CThukQ8b0s" target="_blank"
          >Paddling a Kayak in a Straight Line (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8972 mb-requirement-id-8974">
        (b) Spin or pivot from a stationary position 180 degrees (half circle)
        to the right and left within two boat lengths. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/eKGsnIat1NQ" target="_blank"
          >Fast Sea Kayak Turn—Turning a Sea Kayak 180 Degrees Efficiently
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8972 mb-requirement-id-8975">
        (c) Move abeam to the right 10 feet and to the left 10 feet. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1j1DuKmZk1o" target="_blank"
          >How To Turn a Kayak (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8972 mb-requirement-id-8976">
        (d) Stop the boat in one boat length. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kRUpSLUFMII" target="_blank"
          >Paddle Strokes, the Emergency Stopping Procedure (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8972 mb-requirement-id-8977">
        (e) While maintaining forward motion, turn the kayak 90 degrees to the
        right and left.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8972 mb-requirement-id-8984">
        (f) Move the kayak backward three to four boat lengths using appropriate
        and effective reverse strokes. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/O-feCLPf-qw" target="_blank"
          >Reverse Stroke (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8972 mb-requirement-id-8985">
        (g) Paddle the kayak in a buoyed figure 8 course around markers three to
        four boat lengths apart.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
